Good. Then it needs to stop sounding like a clever metaphor and start reading like a system someone could actually build, audit, and deploy.

OrbitOS / Galaxy Map Spec

Repo- and world-ready version

1. One-line product definition

A privacy-bounded multi-agent trajectory engine that models people, groups, and institutions as evolving state vectors in a shared interaction field, so influence is measured as orbit change over time rather than static connection counts.

That is clean enough for a README and concrete enough for a skeptical builder.

⸻

2. Position it correctly

This is not:
	•	a social graph
	•	a follower map
	•	a vibes engine
	•	a sci-fi “digital soul” model
	•	a total simulation of a person

This is:
	•	a trajectory model
	•	a state-space renderer
	•	an interaction perturbation engine
	•	a temporal influence analysis tool
	•	a bounded digital twin approximation

Use “bounded approximation” everywhere. That phrase will save you from bullshit and from overclaiming.

