23. Final hardened version

Here is the repo-ready framing I would actually put at the top:

OrbitOS is a privacy-bounded trajectory engine for modeling how people, teams, and systems alter one another over time. Instead of treating identity as a static node in a graph, it represents each actor as a bounded state vector moving through a shared interaction field. The result is a map of orbit change, resonance, drift, capture, and perturbation that helps users see where motion is self-directed, socially induced, or system-constrained. OrbitOS does not claim to model the whole person; it models observable trajectory proxies with explicit uncertainty, provenance, and consent boundaries.

That is world-ready.

